Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium heat. Once hot, add half the @butter{30%g}(divided) and allow to melt.

Add the onion, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden and soft, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @sweet potato{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the sweet potato onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, once the onion has softened, add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and half the garlic. Stir together and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @basmati rice{150%g} into the onion and garlic until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Add 1/4 tsp salt and the @water for the rice{300%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}(diced) and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and remaining garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium, then add the @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{15%g}. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir the @peas{120%g}, cooked rice, @honey{1%tbsp} and remaining butter into the frying pan.

Once roasted, stir the sweet potato through the rice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little dry.

When everything's ready, share the Cajun spiced rice between your bowls.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} and top with a drizzle of @soured cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!